    <p>There is nothing on earth more constant nor more changing than the sky.</p>
    <p>Every person on the planet looks up to see the same sky. And yet none of us ever see exactly the same sky twice.</p>
    <p>The sky has inspired mankindâ€™s greatest feats of exploration, has been the source of countless wishes and prayers and dreams. It connects our lives and frames our experiences in a primal way, one that far predates the technology we now insist is our most meaningful way of connecting.</p>
    <p>cirrostratus proposes a new way of using this technology to explore our relationship with the world around us. Rather than use your device to mediate this exchange with your environment, we propose that you simply set it down and focus on the moment in front of you. All the while, you can use that device to be a part of something bigger, to capture something unique and temporal and beautiful.</p>
    <p>We want to take the biggest, most wonderous element in our the world, cram it into your tiny little phone, and then bring it back to life in a piece that celebrates our existence in all its spectacular forms.</p>
